## Copier usage (generated-project docs)

This project was generated with Copier.

### Generating again vs updating

- **`copier recopy`** (or `copier copy` into an existing tree) reapplies the template while keeping answers;
  it does **not** use Copier’s smart merge. Prefer **`copier update`** when you want template changes merged
  with your local edits.

### Updating this project

If the template includes a valid `.copier-answers.yml` file and both the template and this project are versioned with git tags,
then you can update by running:

```bash
copier update
```

Add **`--trust`** if the template uses tasks. Use **`--defaults`** to skip re-prompting. To change one answer:
**`copier update --defaults --data key=value`**, or **`--data-file`**. To refresh answers without changing template version:
**`copier update --vcs-ref=:current:`**.

Check whether a newer template exists: **`copier check-update`** (automation: **`--output-format json`**, **`--quiet`**
exits with code `2` when an update is available).

During updates, Copier compares the template with your project. Unresolved hunks appear as **inline conflict markers**
(default **`--conflict inline`**) or as **`*.rej`** files if you use **`--conflict rej`**. This repo’s pre-commit
config includes **`check-merge-conflict`** and a hook that fails on committed **`*.rej`** files.

When developing a **local** template clone, **`copier copy --vcs-ref HEAD TEMPLATE .`** uses the current working tree
(including uncommitted files); otherwise Copier may select the latest tag instead.

⚠️ Never edit `.copier-answers.yml` manually.

### Trusted templates

Generate projects only from trusted templates, as Copier tasks run with the same level of access as your user.

